  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for Emergency Shelter and Transitional Housing</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project by UNDP is to provide shelter and NFI support for flood affected individuals in the state of Kerela. UNDP will support the housing repairs of 5,000 damaged households throughout three target districts. The project will provide cash grants to targeted households combined with technical assistance to provide guidance to undertake such repairs. UNDP will establish shelter hubs to support the rehabilitation of the houses. Some 24,000 individuals will supported over 6 months.</narrative>
  </description>
